summary: Sorry Baby: A Killing Eve Podcast: Review and Analysis of S1E2: “I’ll Deal with him Later!”
title: Sorry Baby: A Killing Eve Podcast: Review and Analysis of S1E2: “I’ll Deal with him Later!”
body:
Hello KE Fandom!

Apologies for the delay with the second episode, we podcast babies had to get through some technical difficulties, but we are on the other side of the rainbow bridge now! And going forward you should get your fill weekly on Tuesdays!

We are Sorry Baby - a fan-made Killing Eve podcast that is dedicated to peeling back the layers of this totally focussed, and yet, sometimes inaccessible show. Join us, as we deep dive into every episode and find parallels in Eve and Villanelle’s intersections and contradictions.

We are live on ALL platforms: Apple Podcast, Google Podcasts, Stitcher, Amazon - and any other podcast streaming app that you use. To start you off, here is the spotify link: https://open.spotify.com/show/316bpHGUHqPcNSiBzKCW7D

Here is all you need to know:

When will you upload it? Every Tuesday!

Where can we find you? Every Podcast platform!

But, 2 hours - why? Because Eve should have heated that Shepherd’s Pie in the oven! We take our time digging in, and we hope it’s worth yours!

I have so many thoughts, can I share them? Of course! We started this so we could engage with all the brilliant fans out there. Reach us at: killingeveflyonthewall@gmail.com, DM us here on reddit, Twitter: @sorrybabypod, Tumblr: https://sorrybabypodcast.tumblr.com/

We want all your feedback, all your enthusiasm, and all your questions! Did we miss anything you picked up on? Tell us for a shout out! Please send all thoughts on any of the platforms mentioned above. We are taking in questions for all of Season 1 - so please help us make the listener section a success! And lastly, Subscribe, share, and post reviews wherever you like your voice being heard!

“Do you like listening, or being listened to?” Both.

summary: There are so many fucking parallels between Killing Eve and Hannibal I thought there were intense parallels in the first season?...
body:
There are so many fucking parallels between Killing Eve and Hannibal

I thought there were intense parallels in the first season? Bitch, I was not ready for the second season!

I refuse to believe that at least some of these parallels aren’t intentional. There are two many, and it works so well if you look at it as one piece in discussion with another and kinda forming their own subgenre?

Anyway, one day I will write a long post on this, figure out screenshots, and flail around a lot
